<HEADLINE> Palestine Expects U.S. Envoy Middle East Tour to Succeed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of the Palestinian Council
Ahmed Queria said today Palestine hoped that the current Middle
East tour paid by U.S. envoy Dennis Ross would succeed.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Egyptian Sawt Al-Arab Radio, Queria
said the tour of Ross was expected to succeed so as to pave the
way for U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's visit to the
region at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Palestinian side would brief Ross on its
standpoint about the current situation of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Queria described the deadlock over the Middle East peace as
"very dangerous", saying the peace process will not achieve its
objectives unless the Israeli government halts the building of
Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem and lifts the punitive
sanctions imposed on the Palestinians following the two suicide
bombing attacks in West Jerusalem on July 30.
</P>
<P>
Ross arrived in Israel on Saturday, whose tour was reported to
aim at providing an appropriate atmosphere for Albright to visit
the Middle East at the end of this month as well as strengthening
security cooperation between Israel and Palestine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
