<HEADLINE> Komen Wins Men's 5,000m Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Daniel Komen of Kenya won the men's
5,000 meters gold medal at the 6th World Athletics Championships here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
His winning time was 13 minutes 07.38 seconds, ahead of Khalid
Boulami of Morocco's 13:09.34 and Tom Nyariki of Kenya's 13:11.09.
</P>
<P>
Komen, who had beaten the 13-minute-barrier three times this season
before the meet with a personal best of 12:48.98, control the race
completely from the gun to the finish. His leading position was never
challenged before winning his first world title with time to spare.
</P>
<P>
Boulami, 1992 Olympic champion, denied a Kenya 1-2 finish when he
outkicked Nyariki on the home straight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
