<HEADLINE> Kuwait Raps Israel for Escalating Mideast Tension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait today accused
Israel of escalating the Middle East tension and urged the
international community to press the Jewish state to put
the peace process back on track.
</P>
<P>
After a weekly session chaired by Kuwaiti acting Prime
Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah, Kuwaiti cabinet said in
a statement that Israel's activities in southern Lebanon,
Palestinian autonomous areas and Jerusalem would further
complicate the already tense situation in the region and thwart
current efforts to revive the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the international community,
especially the Unites States and Russia, co-sponsors of the peace
process, should pressure Israel to stop its "arbitrary" measures
against the Palestinians and step up efforts to salvage the peace process.
</P>
<P>
In reaction to the Jerusalem suicide bombings on July 30, in
which 15 people were killed and 170 others wounded, Israel has
closed the Palestinian self-ruled areas of the West Bank and
Gaza Strip and imposed crippling economic sanctions upon them.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks have been deadlocked since
Israel began the construction of a Jewish settlement in East
Jerusalem in March this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
