<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Gold Output Rises in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Gold production in South
Africa rose by 5.2 percent in June to 39,140 kg from 37,168 kg in
the previous month, the Chamber of Mines announced at the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
On a year-by-year basis, chamber production in June rose 204
kg or 0.5 percent from the 3,893 kg produced in the same month in
1996, the chamber said.
</P>
<P>
Production so far this year has reached 241,581 kg, or 2.3
percent down compared with the 247,096 kg produced in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Non-chamber producers' output measured 736 kg this June
compared with the 753 kg registered in May, the chamber said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is the biggest gold producer and exporter in the
world. However, its gold output has been declining in recent
years. For this, the chamber sealed a contract with gold miners
last month in which it promised to raise the miners' pay in
return for their pledge to increase 90 tons of gold this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970811.0039 </DOCNO>
