<HEADLINE> British Princess Ends Visit to Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sarajevo, August 10 (Xinhua) -- British princess Diana on
Sunday ended a three-day visit to Bosnia as part of her world-wide
campaign to spotlight human sufferings from landmines.
</P>
<P>
The visit of the divorced princess was sponsored by the
Washington-based landmine survivors' network and took her to
Tuzla, Zenica and Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, she had met with victims of landmines, some
of them children, rehabilitation facilities and former frontlines.
</P>
<P>
In more than three years of the Bosnian war which ended in
1995, an estimated three millions of mines had been laid across
the country by fighting ethnic foes and a fraction of them have
since been dismantled. 
