<HEADLINE> S.Africa Imposes New Arms Embargo on Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The South African government has
ordered a ban on the sale of 12 Rooivalk helicopters to Turkey due
to Ankara's Cyprus policy and human rights record.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper Daily News said today that the decision was
made for fear that the South Africa-manufactured choppers might be
used in Cyprus or Turkey's military operation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that South Africa's Sunday Independent Daily
quoted Kader Asmal, chairman of the board which imposed the new
arms embargo on Ankara, as saying that this move could be seen as
a protest against Turkey's Cyprus policy and its poor human rights
situation.
</P>
<P>
Denel, the Rooivalk-type helicopter producer, however, has
reportedly planned to do more arms business with Turkey, which is
making efforts to enhance its defense capacity.
</P>
<P>
The South African government lifted a previous arms blockade in
April, which was imposed following a massive Turkish military
incursion in northern Iraq to strike outlawed Kuridsh Workers'
Party rebels there in 1995. 
</P>
