<HEADLINE> Xinhua HK Branch Holds Reception on Chief's Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000 people from
all walks of life in Hong Kong attended a reception given by the
Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch this evening to bid farewell
to its former director Zhou Nan and welcome its new director Jiang
 Enzhu.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, who came to work in Hong Kong as Xinhua Hong Kong
Branch chief in February 1990, said at the reception that it was
"the greatest delight" in his life to take part in and witness the
 return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The "one country, two systems" concept has now become a reality
 in Hong Kong, he said, adding that future developments will prove
 the great vitality of this concept.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said that during the past seven years or so he got to know
 Hong Kong people's love of their motherland, and their
industriousness, wisdom and enterprising spirit had left an
indelible impression on him.
</P>
<P>
He said that he had made friends with many people in different
walks of life in Hong Kong and established profound friendship
with them. This friendship, he said, will live for ever.
</P>
<P>
He also wished the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) government headed by Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa new
successes in their work to maintain sustained prosperity and
stability in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Enzhu, former Chinese ambassador to Britain who came here
 on August 6 to replace Zhou, spoke highly of Zhou Nan's fruitful
work in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that with Hong Kong's return, the functions of Xinhua
News Agency Hong Kong Branch "will be adjusted appropriately". It
"will not interfere in the affairs which fall in the domain of the
 high-degree autonomy of the Hong Kong SAR" and it "will continue
to maintain extensive contacts with people in different walks of
life in Hong Kong and make its own contributions in enhancing the
contacts and exchanges between Hong Kong and the inland areas," he
 stated.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed the conviction that Hong Kong people will
surely build a better future under the leadership of the SAR
government and with the backing of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa expressed heartfelt thanks to
Zhou Nan and extended a warm welcome to Jiang Enzhu on behalf of
the SAR government and Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that Hong Kong got to an inspiring start in
implementing the principles of "one country, two systems," "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong" with a high degree of autonomy. A
 host of facts after the establishment of the SAR on July 1 have
shown the Central Government's determination to carry out these
principles, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the reception were vice chairmen of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference Ann Tse-kai and Henry Fok Ying-tung and representatives
 of the SAR government, the Executive Council, the Provisional
Legislative Council, the People's Liberation Army Hong Kong
Garrison and the Commissioner's Office of the Chinese Foreign
Ministry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
