<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdul Meguid said today that the Arab organization fully
supports Syria, and that it categorically rejects Israeli threats
to Syria.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the media today, he strongly attacked the
Israeli government led by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu for
intimating that a war would be waged between Israel and Syria.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Meguid said the Israeli government has gone beyond all
limits by imposing unfair siege on the Palestinian people, and by
repeatedly violating Lebanese sovereignty. In so doing, he said,
Israel is indicating its unwillingness to resume the Middle East
peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Meguid pointed out that any effort or initiative ought to
tackle the root causes of the tension in the region, including
Israel's settlement expansion, tampering with religious beliefs,
and imposition of unjust siege on the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
He called on the U.S. administration to undertake a neutral and
fair role in the peace process, demanding attention be
concentrated on the core of the problem rather than its fringes.
</P>
<P>
Three Katyousha rockets fired from south Lebanon landed in
northern Israel last Friday, wounding three people. Israel has
held Syria responsible for the rocket attack, saying whoever
launched the rockets, the terrorists were working for Syria.
