<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Holds Talks With US Presidential Assistant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Liu Huaqiu, director of the
State Council's Foreign Affairs Office, had a lengthy meeting with
Samuel R. Berger, assistant to the U.S. President for National
Security Affairs, in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that developing a stable and healthy
Sino-U.S. relationship is in the fundamental interests of both
countries and the world at large, and the two sides will continue
to make active efforts toward this end.
</P>
<P>
The talks on Sino-U.S. relations and some major international
issues started this morning and lasted until late in the
afternoon, with both sides expressing their views on President
Jiang Zemin's state visit to the U.S. this fall.
</P>
<P>
Both sides emphasized the significance of the visit, saying
that the two countries should work together to prepare for this
visit and to ensure its success, so that the Sino-US relationship
will enter into a new period of development on the eve of the new
century.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that the 21st century has great
hope. Although the world still faces many challenges, detente and
co-operation are becoming the main stream of international
relations.
</P>
<P>
In the new international situation, they said, the two
countries, which share many important interests, hope to maintain
world peace and stability and avoid the chaos of wars, and are
ready to increase strategic dialogues and co-operation. They
expressed the hope for peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific
region and economic co-operation and development. Preventing the
spread of nuclear weapons and other weapons of mass destruction is
a common goal of the two countries, they pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The two countries' economies have become more complementary and
bilateral exchanges in education, science and technology continue
to grow.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have maintained effective co-operation in
fighting international crimes, drug trafficking, illegal
immigration and international terrorism.
</P>
<P>
As two environmental and energy powers, China and the US should
tighten co-operation on environmental protection, which is of
great significance to both sides and to the rest of the world,
they emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu said that both sides should have a positive and
realistic attitude toward differences between the two
countries. As long as both sides strictly abide by the principles
of the three Sino-U.S. joint communiques and consider the overall
circumstances of the bilateral relationship, conduct dialogue on
equal footing, avoid differences, reinforce co-operation oriented
towards the future, there are many prospects for bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Berger said the U.S. side is willing to collaborate with the
Chinese in making new progress in the bilateral relationship.
</P>
<P>
Berger is here as a guest of the Chinese Foreign Ministry for a
three-day visit. He is expected to meet top Chinese leaders
tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
