<HEADLINE> More Foreign Investment In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The amount of foreign capital
China used in the first seven months of 1997 reached 26 billion
dollars, up 15.75 percent from the same period last year, in spite
of a decrease in the number of enterprises approved to use foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), in the first seven months of this year,
11,487 enterprises were approved to deal directly with foreign
funds. This involved 26.124 billion US dollars of contractural
investment, down 46.16 percent compared with the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
However, actual use of foreign funds by these enterprises
climbed 8.9 percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC sources said the solely foreign-owned enterprises and
Sino-foreign joint ventures used a considerably larger amount of
foreign capitals, with increases of 26.65 and 15.02 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, China also took in 1.7
billion US dollars of foreign investment from other foreign
capital sources, 9.59 times more than for the same period of last
year. These include international leasing, compensation trade and
processing and assembling with imported parts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
