<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Worst Fighting Breaks out in Somalia Since May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
three others wounded when armed militiamen exchanged heavy fire
at the ex-control junction via Afgoe of south Mogadishu Sunday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to an eyewitness, the fighting started when a convoy
of vehicles transporting khat from the K-50 airstrip and escorted
by battle wagons were attacked by other militiamen trying to loot
the khat.
</P>
<P>
Reports said all three victims killed in the attack were
combatant militiamen, while the wounded were civilians caught in
the cross fire. The fighting subsided as each side of the
militiamen ran for defense.
</P>
<P>
Attacks on the khat kiosks by gunmen are frequent, but this
one was the most serious since south Mogadishu returned to
relative calmness following the agreement between the factions
led by Osman Ali Atto and Hussein Aidid in May this year.
</P>
