<HEADLINE> Beijing Symposium on Diabetes Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Doctors from China's 13
provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions gathered in
Beijing today to discuss ways to treat diabetes by combining
traditional Chinese and Western medicine.
</P>
<P>
The treatment of gallstones, kidney stones and liver stones
will also be discussed at the seven-day symposium, which is
sponsored by the Chinese Society of the Integration of Traditional
Chinese and Western Medicines.
</P>
<P>
Participants, who are mostly from under-developed parts of
central and western China, will discuss research developments,
especially simple therapies that could easily be used in rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
They will receive special training by Beijing Asian Games
Village Hospital, one of China's best hospitals for treating
diabetes and gallstones and similar cases. It has been approved
to accept foreign patients since 1993.
</P>
<P>
China has had an increase in the number of people suffering
from these diseases in the past few years. About 10 percent of
Chinese suffer from gallstones, kidney stones, or liver stones and
six percent have diabetes problems. Most live in the
under-developed rural areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
