<HEADLINE> Lucent's Millionth Switching Gear Line In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Lucent Technologies, the leading
US telecommunications company, announced today in Beijing that it
has installed the one millionth line of one of the world's most
technically sophisticated switches in China.
</P>
<P>
Randy Yeh, president of Lucent Technologies (China) Co., Ltd.,
said that it was installed in a telephone switching center in
Qingdao, a coastal city in Shandong Province, on July 24, and will
support more than 35,000 phone lines.
</P>
<P>
The 5ESS-2000 was developed by Bell Laboratories, the R and D
arm of Lucent Technologies, at the start of the 1990s, and is used
in more than 50 countries and regions, and is known for its
outstanding transmission capacity and speed.
</P>
<P>
Lucent has installed 5ESS switching machines with 6.5 million
accesses in China. The switching system is assembled in two
centers: the US's Oklahoma City, and Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
Lucent Technologies Qingdao Telecom Equipment Co., a joint
venture funded by Lucent and China's Ministry of Post and
Telecommunications, has a manufacturing capacity of 1.5 million
lines annually, and has sold four million 5ESS machines in 16
provinces and municipalities in China. The joint venture now makes
up five percent of the switching machine market here.
</P>
<P>
Yeh said that Lucent Technologies will expand technology
transfers in China to establish a "strategic partnership" with
China's telecom sector, one of the fastest growing in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
