<HEADLINE> Two Million Ugandans Tested HIV Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Two million Ugandans have been
tested to be HIV positive this year, "The Monitor" reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Jotham Musinguzi, director of the Population Secretariat,
revealed to a meeting of National Organisation of Trade Union on
Friday that the contraction rate of the killer virus among
females 15 to 19 years of age is six times more than their male
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
An early report said that over 8,500 people were infected with
HIV virus daily in Uganda. And 84 percent of AIDS infections
occurred through unprotected sexual intercourse in the country,
with 25 to 40 percent of children population contracting HIV/AIDS
from infected mothers.
</P>
<P>
Although AIDS awareness is between 95 to 99 percent in Uganda,
said Nathen Bakyayita, official from the country's MInistry of
Health, there has been no behavoural change. 
</P>
