<HEADLINE> Thailand to Export Chickens to Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Thailand for the first time will
start to export chickens to Canada this year, according to the
Thai Commerce Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency has granted the
certificates to five Thai companies for exports of chickens to
Canada, the foreign trade department under the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Thai exporters will have to meet high quarantine
standards and pass tight examinations by Canada, which blocked
Thai chicken products' entry into Canada in the past, the
department said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand exported 12 billion baht (480 million U.S. dollars)
worth of frozen chickens and chicken products last year. The Thai
Commerce Ministry has set a target of 13 billion baht for this
year.  
</P>
