<HEADLINE> APEC Human Resource Development Symposium in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A three-day '97 Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) Symposium on telecommunications sector
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by China's Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications
(MPT) and APEC Telecommunication Working Group, the symposium,
which is attended by senior telecom officials and delegates from
APEC, is expected to touch on potential co-operation in human
resource development in the telecom sector, an industry in need of
well-trained employees.
</P>
<P>
Also on the agenda are long-distance education, vocational
education for the telecom industry, multimedia technology, and a
human resource database.
</P>
<P>
A number of countries in the Asia-Pacific region have achieved
rapid growth in recent years and the trade volume of 18 members
accounted for 46 percent of the world's total. The telecom
industry, a pioneer in the region's economic growth, needs to be
developed.
</P>
<P>
Lin Jiquan, vice-minister of MPT, said in the opening speech
that the speedy development of China's telecom industry shows
that telecom moderization should rely on scientific advancement
and good employees.
</P>
<P>
China's posts and telecom industry in 1996 employed a total of
1.2 million full and part-time workers, with the per-capita labor
productivity of 119,000 yuan, or 29.6 percent more than in
1995. The target set by MPT is 220,000 yuan in the year 2000, he
said. 
</P>
