<HEADLINE> US Exports to UAE Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. exports to the United
Arab Emirates (UAE) have jumped to 1.11 billion U.S. dollars in
the first five months of this year, according to a trade report
here today.
</P>
<P>
This was a 229-million-dollar increase compared with 881
million dollars in the same period of last year, the report
released by the U.S. Embassy in Abu Dhabi said.
</P>
<P>
The overall U.S. exports to the UAE in 1996 were 2.52 billion
dollars, up from 1.99 billion dollars in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
U.S. exports to the UAE include equipment for the oil and gas
industry, for the aviation sector and a host of other industrial
and consumer products.
</P>
<P>
The report also showed U.S. imports from the UAE increased
from 218.4 million dollars during January-May period in 1996 to
487.7 million dollars in the first five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
U.S. imports from the UAE were only 537.9 million dollars in
the whole year of 1996 while in 1995, the import figure stood at
485.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the UAE was the second largest trading partner with
the U.S. in the Middle East region following Saudi Arabia.
</P>
</TEXT>
