<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index fell 50.06 points to below the 1900-point psychological
resistance line and closed at 1893.86 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 240.43 million units, worth 520.53
million Singapore dollars (about 356.52 million U.S. dollars).
Declines overwhelmed advances by 348 to 25, while 240 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
