<HEADLINE> South Korea's Seoul Mayor to Run for Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Mayor of Seoul, Cho Soon, has
decided to run for the country's presidency, representing the
Democratic Party (DP), the former president of the minor
opposition party, Lee Ki-taek, said today.
</P>
<P>
Lee said Cho Soon asked the DP on Sunday to postpone its
national convention to nominate its presidential candidate. "The
request means Cho has solidified his bid to run as the DP's
candidate."
</P>
<P>
After a high-level meeting, DP officials said today the party
supported the bid of Cho, who told a staff meeting of the City
Hall today that he would leave his present office to campaign for
the presidency in December.
</P>
<P>
The main rivals facing the DP candidate are Lee Hoi-chang of
the ruling New Korea Party, veteran politician Kim Dae-jung
representing the National Congress for New Politics, and Kim
Jong-pil of the United Liberal Democrats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
