<HEADLINE> Thompson Beats Le in Pan Pacific Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- American Jenny Thompson edged
Chinese world record holder Le Jingyi in the 100 meters freestyle
final at the Pan Pacific swimming championships in Fukuoka on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old American clocked a new meet record time of
54.82 seconds, beating Le into second place by 0.04 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Thompson's teammate Catherine Fox finished third in 56.07.
</P>
<P>
Samantha Riley of Australia, 1994 world champion, emerged
winner from the women's 100 meters breaststroke final where she
clocked a new meet mark of 1:07.81.
</P>
<P>
South African Penny Heyns timed 1:08.65 for second spot with
American Kristy Kowal third at 1:09.18
</P>
<P>
Kurt Grote of the United States, who set a championship record
in the men's 100 meters breastroke heats, went on to win the final
by bettering it with a time of 1:01.22.
</P>
<P>
Phil Rogers of Australia, the former record holder, came second
in 1:01.85 and American Jarrod Marrs was third in 1:02.64.
</P>
<P>
The men's 100 meters freestyle title went to Michael Klim of
Australia, who clocked 49.46. He beat Neil Walker of the United
States by 0.11 seconds and Ricardo Busquets of Puerto Rico by
0.48. 
</P>
</TEXT>
