<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Reports Latest HIV Infection Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-four persons were found
to be HIV carriers in the second quarter of 1997, bringing the
total number of reported HIV infections in Hong Kong to 855, the
Department of Health announced today.
</P>
<P>
With 11 more AIDS cases reported in the same period, the total
number of confirmed cases added up to 274.
</P>
<P>
Up to 80 percent of the HIV carriers were infected through
sexual contacts, and the rest acquired the infection through
contaminated blood or mother-to-child transmission.  
</P>
</TEXT>
