<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Sets Up Homepage for Natural Scenery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Internet surfers now can gain
access to Hong Kong's country parks and marine parks through
homepage newly opened by the government.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Hong Kong Agriculture and Fisheries
Department said today that details of individual country parks,
marine parks, nature trails, hiking trails and other recreational
facilities such as barbecue sites are provided on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Densely populated with 6.3 million people on an area of around
1,000 sq. km, Hong Kong has earmarked 40 percent of its land as
country parks for outdoor recreational and nature conservation
purposes.
</P>
<P>
Through the homepage, users can obtain hints on hiking safety,
statistics related to country parks and marine parks, and useful
telephone numbers, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
In addition to more than 1,000 color pictures and maps, there
are 20 real-time videos with sound tracks in English, Cantonese
and Putonghua on the homepage.  
</P>
