<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people including a
political party leader were injured in four separate bomb
explosions in South India's Tamil Nadu since Sunday night, Press
Trust of India (PIT) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Two consecutive bomb explosions in the communally sensitive
town of Rajapalayam Sunday night left 10 people injured. Two more
bomb blasts rocked the Russian Cultural Center and the Tamil Nadu
State Election Commission in Chennai, capital of Tamil Nadu, today
leaving two more people wounded.
</P>
<P>
Handbills recovered from both the blast sites in Chennai last
night indicated that the Tamil Nadu Liberation Party, a small
extremist group, was behind the explosions.
</P>
<P>
