<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Businesses in Fujian Enjoy Sound Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Overseas businesses in east
China's Fujian province are doing better this year than last year,
according to a survey by the provincial statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau questioned 53 major overseas-funded businesses and
found that they made a combined profit of 125 million yuan during
the first half of the year, 21.5 percent more than the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
However, the operating costs of these firms went down, and
their operating cost and income ratio dropped at a rate of 9.6
percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that the firms' average scale of assets rose
17.9 percent, standing at 490 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, their intellectual property is valued at 485 million
yuan, a rise of 56.3 percent. The increase rate of intellectual
property is much higher than the rates of liquid and fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that workers' efficiency also improved
during this period: An average laborer turned out 83,400
yuan-worth of goods, an increase of 18.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
