<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has granted some
170 million U.S. dollars of fund for infrastructure projects in
the Philippines' 30 agrarian reform communities in 10 provinces
nationwide, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The aid project is aimed at bolstering the country's
agricultural productivity and improving the lifestyle of marginal
farmers in the countryside, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Agrarian Reform Secretary Ernesto Garilao as
saying that the project will be supervised by the Agrarian Reform
Communities Development Project in the next six years.
</P>
<P>
The project includes community development and technical
assistance, rural infrastructure and enterprise development, he
said.
</P>
<P>
