<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 11 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldier was killed and
another wounded today in south Lebanon in an ambush attack launched
by Hezbollah gunmen, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred in the area of Mleikh, south of Jezzine in the
eastern sector of Israel-claimed south Lebanon security zone. The
Hezbollah gunmen fired from ambush at a unit of Israeli Army's elite
Golani infantry unit on patrol duty and wounded two soldiers, one of
them died shortly.
</P>
<P>
Israeli aircraft and artillery immediately retaliated for the
attack by bombing Hezbollah positions in the central and southern
areas of the security zone. No casualities were reported.
</P>
<P>
The latest clash sparked fears of imminent wisdespread battles in
south Lebanon, where the fighting has been escalating in the past
week during which 14 Lebanese and one Israeli soldier was killed.
</P>
<P>
Israel warned that if Hezbollah continued its indiscriminate
shelling, the ceasefire understandings reached last April will
disintegrate.
</P>
<P>
The ceasefire accord, brokered by the United States following
Israel's Operation Grapes of Wrath, stipulated that both sides should
not target civilians in military attacks.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the 1,100-kilometer security zone in 1985 to protect
its northern border from cross border attack. 
</P>
