<HEADLINE> Residents Relocated From Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The relocation of people
living in the area of the gigantic Three Gorges project has
entered its most critical phase.
</P>
<P>
Wanxian city on the site of the project recently signed a
letter of responsibility with Chongqing, which is administering
the resettlement effort, to ensure success of the process.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the Three Gorges project will affect three
counties in Wanxian and 11,355 people, including 2,699
farmers. Thirteen towns and 73 factories will have to be rebuilt.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the letter, the city's investment in the
relocation effort will reach 304 million yuan (about 38 million US
dollars) by the end of this year, and some 7,286 rural residents
will be resettled, and 40,000 sq.m. of housing reconstructed.
</P>
<P>
According to a local official, in the first half of this year,
Wushan county, one of the three in the project area, has invested
41.63 million yuan, resettled 2,462 residents, and rebuilt ten
factories. The relocation process in the other two counties is
also going well.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges project was officially launched in December
1994, and is scheduled to last for 17 years. More than one million
people will be relocated.
</P>
<P>
The resettlement, the largest for a project of this kind in
history, is scheduled to cost 40 billion yuan. It will be
completed in 2009.  
</P>
</TEXT>
