<HEADLINE> White Tortoise Returns to Wild in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A white tortoise which had
been cared for by humans for 13 years in Huaiyang county in
central China's Henan Province was set free last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On August 14, 1984, a local boy who was fishing in a lake
caught a white tortoise by mistake. The 650-gram female was a
milky-white color, and according to an expert, was about 250 years
old.
</P>
<P>
So the county built a shed for it that approximated the natural
environment, and assigned personnel to take care of it.
</P>
<P>
In the past 13 years, the weight of the tortoise has increased
50 grams, and although it has laid 24 eggs, no tortoises have
hatched, because the eggs were not fertilized.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of people have visited the white tortoise,
but in order to give it a more natural life and to allow it to
breed, the county authorities sent it back to the lake where it
was caught. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
