<HEADLINE> More Laid-off Workers Re-settled in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
province has found new jobs for 97,500 laid-off workers in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
With government help, some enterprises and companies provided
jobs for 37 percent of the unemployed workers, and 42 percent
found jobs in the service sector locally. The other 21 percent
became self-employed laborers, according to officials from Hebei
Labor Department.
</P>
<P>
The department expects that the province will need to find more
than one million jobs for the urban unemployed by the end of the
year 2002.
</P>
<P>
Provincial departments plan to raise some 400 million yuan
(48.2 million US dollars) in re-employment funds, and the labor
department is encouraging companies to employ the workers.
</P>
<P>
Over 180,000 of them have been given training at training
centers established with unemployment insurance funds set aside by
the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
A total of 152 job search agencies have also played an
important role in finding jobs. 
