<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches 1st Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka today launched its
first industrial park with international standard in Western
province of the country.
</P>
<P>
According to Industrial Development Ministry sources, with a
total area of 168 hectares, the Seethawaka Industrial Park is set
up by Kumagia Cumi of Japan, at a cost of over 33.9 million US
dollars which is funded by the Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund
of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The sources pointed out that the park, located at Avissaweela
about 40 kilometers southeast of Colombo, will create 40,000 jobs
directly or indirectly when completed.  
</P>
