<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Classed As Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The International Human Rights
Commission (IHRC) has identified the Sri Lankan Tamil rebels of
the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) as a terrorist
organization.
</P>
<P>
A statement of the IHRC reaching here today, said the IHRC's
Chairman Mohamad Sahid Amin Khan has declared the LTTE as a
terrorist organization.
</P>
<P>
He has urged the LTTE to stop all acts of terrorism and stop
immediately the killing of non-combatants and cease other human
rights abuses.
</P>
<P>
The violence and terrorism perpetrated by the LTTE are totally
unacceptable to the whole world and the IHRC will support the Sri
Lanka government against LTTE terrorism, he said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
The IHRC also welcomed the steps taken by President Chandrika
Kumaratunga for the cause of human rights according to world needs
and hopes.
</P>
<P>
The IHRC will help the Sri Lanka government to protect and
uphold the Human Rights World Declaration, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan LTTE rebels have been fighting a 14-year war
for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country.
More than 55,000 people were killed in the civil war, according to
 official reports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
