<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi State Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's State Minister for
Local Government and Rural Development Syed Abul Hossain resigned
on Sunday as a sequel to his controversial trip to Singapore by
using green passport instead of the red one, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet Secretary Ataul Huq confirmed the report today and said
that there are certain formalities for acceptance of the
resignation.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the state minister had submitted his
resignation letter after being asked to do so by Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina.
</P>
<P>
Abul Hossain went to Singapore on August 3 without permission
from the prime minister which is required as per the law and used
green passport to leave the country although he had been in
possession of the official red passport.
</P>
<P>
According to the law in the country, holding of two passports
as well as leaving the country without obtaining the government
order are illegal.
</P>
<P>
The issue of the state minister's controversial trip to
Singapore had embarrassed the government as it was the talk of the
town during the last few days.  
</P>
