<HEADLINE> China Improves Aviation Design Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Aviation corporation, a
major Chinese spare parts manufacturer for Boeing aircraft, has
started using computer-aided designing (CAD) technology in its
manufacturing process.
</P>
<P>
The company first used CAD technology in the overall
manufacturing process of the tail surface for the Boeing 737-700,
signifying an aviation industrial design technology leap for China.
</P>
<P>
CAD has greatly improved the efficiency of industrial design in
the company. It now takes only two months for them to design the
tail surface with the new technology, a job that used to take
nearly half a year for them to do by hand.
</P>
<P>
CAD technology has also been widely used by the company for
other airplanes and aviation industry products. 
</P>
