<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Plays Scoreless Soccer with El Salvador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica had to settle for a
scoreless draw with El Salvador on Sunday despite their man
advantage for the final 41 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The game witnessed three players to be kicked out of the pitch
for rough confrontation.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica was first given the opportunity in the 40th minute
when Salvadoran forward Luis Oscar Lazo was expelled for a clash
against Costa Rican captain Ronaldo Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
However, Gonzalez also received the axe with three minutes into
the second half when he failed to wait for Honduran referee Nelson
Calix's signal to restart play on a free kick.
</P>
<P>
One minute later, the referee fished out a second yellow card
against Salvadoran defender Jorge Rodriguez, forcing the visitors
to play the rest with nine men.
</P>
<P>
The scoreless draw left Costa Rica in second place in the final
round in the CONCACAF World Cup qualifying where Mexico clinched
the top spot with 11 points on 3-2-0.
</P>
<P>
In the six-team zone, Costa Rica ranked second currently on
2-2-2 for eight points, followed by the United States with six
points on 1-3-1 and El Salvador six points from 1-3-2.
</P>
<P>
The other teams in the group were Canada who had five points on
1-2-2 and Jamaica with five points on 1-2-2.
</P>
<P>
Only the top three squads qualify for the World Cup finals in
France next summer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
