<HEADLINE> China Makes to Hockey World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 10 (Xinhua) -- China, without its two leading
players and manager, claimed the last place in the next year's
World Cup in the Netherlands with a 3-0 win against Ireland here
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Yu Shu Zhen, Yang Hong Bing and manager Li Xiao Sheng were
suspended for the rest of the tournament for their conducts in the
previous game against Scotland.
</P>
<P>
In the game against Ireland, Ying Liu became the savior by
scoring once in each half. Her powerful drive down the right also
enabled Jian Bin Chen to score the third in the 63rd minute to put
the result beyond doubt.
</P>
<P>
China now faces England on Tuesday in the 5/6th place
play-off. 
</P>
