<HEADLINE> Japan Dethrones Cuba in Baseball Intercontinental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Japan dethroned Cuba 11-2 to take
the baseball Intercontinental Cup in Barcelona on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Japan jumped to a three-run first-inning lead and enjoyed 6-0
advantage after two innings before Uehara Kohji struck three to
earn the victory.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Japan ended the Caribbeans 10-year-old reign
on the Intercontinental Cup.
</P>
<P>
In another surprise of the day, Australia got a bases-loaded
walk in the 10th to beat the United States 7-6 for third place.
</P>
<P>
The United States led 4-1 after the fourth inning and 5-1
heading into the bottom of the seventh.
</P>
<P>
But Adam Burton and Paul Gonzales each cracked two-run homers
to tie it for Australia before American pitcher Robbie Morrison
gave away the victory by walking Clayton Byrne with two outs in
the 10th. 
</P>
