<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik President Calls for Peaceful Settlement of  Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali Rkhmonov
today called for peaceful settlement of the conflicts which
occurred Sunday in some Tajik regions and Dushanbe,according to
the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the Security Council which discussed
the social and political situation in the country, the president
said those who provoke military opposition are linked with the
economic mafia, narcomafia and the criminal world.
</P>
<P>
All the conflicts should be settled through negotiations,
Rakhmonov stressed.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov called on servicemen of the country's armed forces
not to yield to the influence of criminal groups and to keep away
from criminal actions.
</P>
<P>
The president called on the local people to render assistance
to law-enforcement authorities to stem organized crime and armed
mafia.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council had taken measures to ensure and restore
law and order in Dushanbe and adjacent regions and in southern
districts of the Khatlon region, he said.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday afternoon, an armed clash took place 20 kilometers
south-east of the Tajik city of Kurgan-Tyube (the administrative
center of the Khatlon region) between a military brigade of prompt
reaction and unidentified armed group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
