<DOCNO> XIE19970811.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Wins ATP Championship in Ohio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
of the United States defeated fifth seed Thomas Muster of Austria
6-3, 6-4 in the 2.05 million U.S. dollars ATP Championship at
Mason, Ohio on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who did not drop a single set in the match, won the
top prize of 337,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It was his fifth title of the year. He had previously won at
Wimbledon, the Australian Open, San Jose and Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who also won the tournament in 1992, improved his
record to 35-7 this year, including 25-2 in hardcourt matches.
</P>
<P>
Muster advanced to the final by defeating second seed Michael
Chang of the United States on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian has won 18 of his last 21 hardcourt matches for a
26-5 record on the surface this season. He won two titles this
season, both on hardcourts, namely the Dubai Tennis Open and the
Lipton Championships.
</P>
<P>
The last meeting between Muster and Sampras was in the
semifinals of this year's Australian Open, which Sampras won in
straight sets en route to his title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
