<DOCNO> XIE19970811.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Davenport to Win Los Angeles Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- World number two Monica Seles
of the United States rallied to defeat her compatriot Lindsay
Davenport 5-7, 7-5, 6-4 to win the championship match of the Acura
Classic in Los Angeles on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Seles rallied back from a first set loss and fought from a 4-2
deficit in the third set to win the match.
</P>
<P>
She has compiled a 29-9 record this year and advanced to four
other finals, coming up short each time.
</P>
<P>
The former No. 1 player, who earned 79,000 U.S. dollars for the
victory, was 17-1 all time in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who won the event last year, upset world's number
one Martina Hingis of Switzerland in three sets on Saturday en
route to her outing to the finals.
</P>
<P>
She maintained a record of 36-11 this season, including three
titles in Oklahoma City, Indian Wells, and Amelia Island.
</P>
<P>
Hingis suffered just her second loss in 61 matches this season
and first in 36 hardcourt matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
