<P>
 Seles Beats Davenport to Win Los Angeles Tennis
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- World number two tennis
player, Monica Seles of the United States rallied to defeat her
compatriot Lindsay Davenport by 5-7, 7-5, 6-4 in the championship
match of the Acura Classic at Los Angeles today.
</P>
<P>
Seles came back from a loss in the opening set and tried hard
to rally from a 4-2 deficit in the third set to win the match.
</P>
<P>
She has compiled a 29-9 record this year and had advanced to
four other finals, coming up short each time.
</P>
<P>
The former No. 1 player, who earned 79,000 U.S. dollars for the
victory, is now 17-1 all time in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who won this event last year, upset world's number
one player Martina Hingis of Switzerland in three sets Saturday to
reach the finals.
</P>
<P>
She is 36-11 this season and was competing in her fourth final.
She has already captured titles in Oklahoma City, Indian Wells,
and Amelia Island.
</P>
<P>
Hingis suffered just her second loss in 61 matches this season
and first in 36 hardcourt matches. 
</P>
